race.comment: FIERCE 'N FABULOUS (8) scored her Maiden win comfortably here last time out over today's trip. Is lightly raced and has plenty of scope for improvement. Looks well placed, and looks capable of taking the next step. BUNKER JAKO (1) is third up and ready to fire. Just missed in an Open 3 here before the spell over this trip, and he has a low gate and handy 2kg claim. Kept on the fresh side and is a live chance. SOUTH GEORGIA (3) resumes further improved missing a whisker this track/trip. Races forward and won his only second-up out. Fitter now and should be right in it. MISS LYRA (2) resumed on the synthetic and needed it. Had trialled well and will be sharper today. He delivered in an Open 2 here at his lone second-up run. QUEEN OF MALWA (6) is on a quick backup and third-up won't be far away.
